Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.42,0:00:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Star" is a fascinating word.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can refer to both culprits and actors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.50,0:00:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cell phone with a secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.30,0:00:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with a lot of e-mails, conversations, and tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.13,0:00:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lead to one nearly-impossible case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.88,0:00:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.51,0:00:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.05,0:00:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town changes someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.43,0:01:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really shouldn't send them a message just yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.77,0:01:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess I should just be patient and wait it out, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, a chance to get in contact\Nwith their boss will come sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.53,0:01:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when it does, I'll definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.99,0:02:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.45,0:02:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! You're still in your pajamas?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.45,0:02:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to get dressed\Nsince we have to hurry and get going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.58,0:02:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on... It's not the time to\Nplay around with your cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.08,0:02:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.80,0:02:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.26,0:02:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.67,0:02:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should send Shinichi a message before we head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.88,0:02:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he might come back while we're away, and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.30,0:02:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We're leaving with my dad for his work today."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.64,0:02:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"So I'll be counting on your advice if\Nit ends up being a tough case, okay?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.19,0:02:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... send.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.28,0:02:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.70,0:02:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just got an e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the message I just sent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.25,0:02:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way that can be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely sent it to Shinichi's address, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the timing was too perfect to just be a coincidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.59,0:03:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Strange Family's Request:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.43,0:03:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.69,0:03:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you look inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I didn't look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.02,0:03:16.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It rang because you got an e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.27,0:03:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I just wondered, "Who could that be from?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.65,0:03:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It has to be from the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.03,0:03:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I asked him to repair my Detective Badge!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is from Ran, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So don't tell me she... Don't tell me she...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.59,0:03:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.97,0:03:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you guys have to tag along with me every single time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.09,0:03:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your client requested that you bring your family, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.47,0:03:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after all, we might think of something\Nthat will help in your investigation again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.27,0:03:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think so, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.98,0:03:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the great deductions a certain shameful\Ndetective who's hiding somewhere always comes up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that panicked behavior of his...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.61,0:04:05.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be something\Nsuspicious about that e-mail he got earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.37,0:04:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi must have ran off somewhere with\Nsomeone and didn't want her reading my e-mails...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he told me I couldn't have his cell number, since\Nhe's always "too busy with a case" to answer my calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.13,0:04:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in the end, he gave it to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is always contacting Shinichi on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.38,0:04:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s great deductions...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the fact that he\Nsometimes knows weird things about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.51,0:04:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything matches up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.60,0:04:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That rotten Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive him for\Ntaking advantage of a child like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.57,0:04:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.94,0:04:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd like you to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you could somehow find it by the end of the day...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.16,0:04:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, I can no longer stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.27,0:04:52.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)}Kariya Tomoko (39)\N{\fs12} Client, and Tsugutaka's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? May I ask why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.67,0:04:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.50,0:04:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.66,0:05:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man you're having an affair with\Nls going to send you a e-mail tonight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.26,0:05:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who should "shush".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.43,0:05:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my very jealous husband sees that e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or if my strict father or my husband's talkative\Nbrother happen to see it and tell him about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.89,0:05:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you call your partner right\Naway, and ask him not to e-mail you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The calls are always coming from\Nhim, and the number is withheld.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.61,0:05:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, he has a habit writing me on the\Nweekend, but he rarely reads the mail I send him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I have no means to contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.17,0:05:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a very selfish guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.96,0:05:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there are some like that..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.29,0:05:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Egotistical guys, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.72,0:05:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.05,0:05:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when and where did you lose it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.43,0:05:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.97,0:05:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only noticed it was missing the day\Nbefore yesterday, some time in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.85,0:05:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure someone in this\Nhouse has it in their possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:06:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what makes you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.02,0:06:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried calling my cell phone the moment I lost it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.19,0:06:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And someone answered after ten rings,\Nbut quickly hung up without saying a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.53,0:06:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the sound of my father's wooden flute being\Nplayed rather poorly on the other end of the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.12,0:06:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen, it's that sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.38,0:06:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It certainly is being played poorly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.59,0:06:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my father only plays it in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.92,0:06:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I heard that sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that my cellphone has\Nto be some where aim this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.97,0:06:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But each time l tried calling my cell phone\Nafter that, the person hung up without speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.64,0:06:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, if you ask everyone in the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.65,0:06:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes! Of course, I asked them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.31,0:06:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they all pretended to not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're probably waiting for my sin to be exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.28,0:06:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not very welcomed in this\Nhouse and they all want me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I divorce, I'll have to pay a\Nlot of money for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about contacting your cell-phone\Ncarrier and asking them to cancel your plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.46,0:07:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I did so, the e-mails I kept in\Nmy cell phone memory won't be erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.84,0:07:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I locked my cell phone\Nto prevent this kind of situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.46,0:07:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I terminate my contract with the carrier,\Nsomeone might become suspicious and try to unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.84,0:07:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, what can we do...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.64,0:07:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.81,0:07:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friend from middle school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.40,0:07:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Mori Goro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.19,0:07:28.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is going to have his house built soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.49,0:07:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And heard good things about this house you built,\NFather, so he wanted to visit it for reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.16,0:07:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:38.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)} Kariya Daisaku (68)\N{\fs12} Master of the Kariya Household
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you're welcome to visit as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.37,0:07:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it now. That's why she\Nasked him to come with his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.67,0:07:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall I play a song for you on my wooden flute?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.67,0:07:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that won't be necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.59,0:07:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you recognize your ringtone if we call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it may be on silent, now that I think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.13,0:07:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, call it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, at my age...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.69,0:08:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's annoying to often have to go to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.70,0:08:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.37,0:08:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.95,0:08:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounded like our interlocutor\Nanswered the call and hung up right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.58,0:08:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he didn't seem to be much of a strict person...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.34,0:08:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might look like that, but he's actually pretty scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.80,0:08:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was this one incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.72,0:08:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Father is responsible for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.47,0:08:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,12... years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.89,0:08:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Let's talk to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You're Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s classmate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might you be her ex-boyfriend, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! That's way off the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? So, you're a novelist?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:05.93,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kariya Shigehide (37)\N{\fs11}Second Son of the Kariya Household
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.33,0:09:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not famous yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:08.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: The book reads "The Rest of Spring, by Kariya Shigehide.\NNew TV Drama Green-lit! Based on Kariya Shigehide's Renaissance Story of True Love"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you may hear my name thrown about in\Nthree months time, even if it's just for criticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kariya Shigehide"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The author of those romance novels?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So those novels really are going to be adapted for TV?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.22,0:09:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How surprising! I always pictured you as being a lot older!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's going be made into a drama? How great.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.35,0:09:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.60,0:09:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call! Call!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.90,0:09:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's from my publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.37,0:09:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.16,0:09:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it's not him. It hung up right away again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A meeting right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So let's meet at the family\Nrestaurant in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know, the timing with\Nyour father and now this guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These coincidences just keep on coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:09:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coincidences do occur often, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:04.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? But isn't it called a "coincidence"\Nbecause it's not something that normally happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I guess that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.73,0:10:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But ma'am, for something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.23,0:10:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could investigate on your\Nown if you had another cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me go through the\Nextra work to buy another cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.66,0:10:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm not in a position where I can use money freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And instead of asking a friend, I asked\Nyou, a pro, in order to protect my secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Your husband is an illustrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.79,0:10:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.46,0:10:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't seem to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.63,0:10:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is our chance to do this while he's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.39,0:10:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The string of coincidences\Naren't continuing here, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.31,0:10:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think I've seen this painting before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. It was painted by Kariya Tsugutaka\Nwho used to be renowned for his art.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.23,0:10:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you know my work?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.44,0:10:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you three?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.99,0:11:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're Kariya Tsugutaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I imagined someone much younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As an example, younger are like e-mails...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.44,0:11:11.01,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)}Kariya Tsugutaka (42)\N{\fs11} Elders Son of the Kariya Household
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.50,0:11:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I am like a hand-written letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if that's a guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.26,0:11:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave it. It's probably the publisher\Nwho came to ask for my latest work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:26.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure are ringing a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.77,0:11:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? It wasn't a guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there was nobody when we opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:38.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this kind of thing happen a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.49,0:11:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mistress says it's some child playing pranks, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.12,0:11:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we're stuck, we have nowhere else to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's no need to worry any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.54,0:11:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, I just found my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.96,0:11:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And of course, I'll wire your fee over to you right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.92,0:12:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was such a stupid case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.42,0:12:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep! There are some people like that who\Ndeceive others and laugh about it in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.47,0:12:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're really stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.43,0:12:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.81,0:12:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I sleep at the Professor's house tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.14,0:12:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure... Are you playing games with him again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.15,0:12:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a lot of things I want to\Ntalk about with Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} today!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about if I just spend the evening there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did repair my Detective Badge, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.87,0:12:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What brings you here at this time of night?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.41,0:12:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beyond all sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.54,0:12:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.75,0:12:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow, Ran suspects that I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.21,0:12:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 7:00 PM this evening, the body of a woman\Nwas discovered in a car near the Teimudu River.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.63,0:12:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on articles found at the scene, the\Ndeceased woman was a resident of Haido;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.80,0:12:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kariya Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police has confirmed that it was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.76,0:12:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you see anyone suspicious in\Nthe Haido area, please contact...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.81,0:12:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.40,0:13:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is Kariya Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the forensics team, after\Nhaving been stabbed in the stomach...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.41,0:13:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her head was bludgeoned with a heavy object.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hit in the head after having been stabbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. There's a possibility of\Nthere being more than one culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.33,0:13:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that one person carried both\Nan sharp-edged tool and a blunt weapon, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.42,0:13:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my memory serves me correctly,\Nthere was a case just like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.38,0:13:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her purse and money are nowhere to be\Nfound, so I believe this is a case of robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't affirm that yet, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.77,0:13:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, this is police work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outsiders shouldn't interfere, so please move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.03,0:13:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm an insider par excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.03,0:13:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, that mistress asked for my services.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? The mistress was unfaithful?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.33,0:13:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, it seems that was the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.46,0:13:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So her partner killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.13,0:14:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea of who that person might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.42,0:14:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it... A suspicious-looking\Nmustached man came here today with his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! I believe his name was\N"Mori Goro" or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.35,0:14:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mori Goro?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.14,0:14:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well... About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.73,0:14:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.98,0:14:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you do that to the mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.27,0:14:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I was saying, it's not me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.23,0:14:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mouri Kogoro? The famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I had to conceal my name for various reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So have you already arrested him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who killed Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to disturb you, but can you tell\Nme where you were at 7:30 this evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, me? I remained here the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.09,0:14:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Nakamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.30,0:14:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had been playing his wooden flute from\N7:00 PM to around 8:00 PM, when you arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.72,0:14:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only time the sound stopped was\Nwhen I came to bring his dinner around 7:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.10,0:14:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it was just for a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see him at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, in order to not disturb him when he was playing\Nhis flute, I simply placed his dinner in front of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.70,0:15:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he must have smelled tonight's\Ncurry-rice through the paper-thin door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.62,0:15:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're having curry-rice today, huh?\NHaven't had that for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.83,0:15:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Around 7:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.16,0:15:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.12,0:15:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came back from my appointment at 6:00 PM,\Nand have been working here ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.71,0:15:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure those two can confirm that for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.92,0:15:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.89,0:15:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He turned the room's lights on around 6:30 PM, and we saw\Nhis shadow casting across the paper-thin door ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.68,0:15:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when I brought him his dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.52,0:15:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you didn't see him directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.23,0:15:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He always tells us to not come in while he's working.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.36,0:15:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, is it true that Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why we're investigating now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.08,0:16:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I hope you can hurry up,\Nclose the book on this case, and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.00,0:16:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't concentrate on my work with you\Nloitering in the corridor or asking me all these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.29,0:16:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm amazed... Is that really\Nsomething to say with what just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.67,0:16:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So now we're down to the last\Nremaining resident of this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.93,0:16:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that would be Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.85,0:16:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.31,0:16:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? He didn't even touch his dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.35,0:16:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please answer my questions, Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.61,0:16:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's refusing to tell us anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you're asking me if I have any\Nideas, I can't speak on what I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.32,0:16:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wife and I generally don't speak to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems you didn't even touch your dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling ill or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was just immersed in my work and forgot about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.00,0:16:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you didn't talk to him when you brought it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.38,0:16:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.09,0:16:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think he was in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could smell the sweet scent from his pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:16:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you got what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you have nothing else, please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.06,0:17:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His wife just got murdered,\Nand he's thinking about his work...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.52,0:17:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, those three have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.61,0:17:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. It takes 20 minutes to drive here from the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.11,0:17:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's impossible for them to have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.14,0:17:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This means it comes down to her\Npartner being the main suspect, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we don't know who he is or where he could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we try asking Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nfriends to follow the trail back to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.92,0:17:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.54,0:17:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is the Kariya residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.17,0:17:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um... A call for Madam Tomoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.34,0:17:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry the hell up and put Tomoko on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.64,0:17:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't reply to my e-mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.06,0:17:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the police. What's your\Nrelationship with Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.77,0:17:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.94,0:17:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.11,0:17:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.94,0:17:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.11,0:17:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems her partner is working\Nat a bar in Hokkaido right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.07,0:18:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't answer the e-mails and\Nvoice messages he left on her cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.91,0:18:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he got mad and decided to call her home number.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he didn't know about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.29,0:18:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Inspector, it's only one or two\Nhours from here to Hokkaido by plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he caught a flight\Nimmediately after committing the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there were colleagues there with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they started to drink at 8:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.14,0:18:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he couldn't have perpetrated the murder, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.18,0:18:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, who on earth could have?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.77,0:18:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's a peculiar household.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.81,0:18:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three of them eat their\Nmeals separately in their own rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.02,0:18:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:38.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But everyone ate their meals together as\Na family until what happened 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.28,0:18:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,12 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.20,0:18:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would always eat together when\Ntheir third son, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, was still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.66,0:18:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.87,0:18:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kariya Eisuke...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.04,0:18:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! I remember now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.84,0:18:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that case from 12 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.96,0:18:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.75,0:18:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was one, 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.88,0:19:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A case with very similar circumstances to our current case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.26,0:19:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fianc√©e, Aida Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.27,0:19:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, she was\Nbludgeoned to death after having been stabbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} originally was under suspect\Nbecause we couldn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.52,0:19:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, since we found a large pool\Nof his blood next to the phone booth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all the money in his bank\Naccount was withdrawn just after the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.58,0:19:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We concluded someone had kidnapped Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand murdered him once they got his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.58,0:19:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the crime scene was a\Nrather infrequently visited place...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.46,0:19:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the investigation ended due to a lack of witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I recall, we got a call\Nfrom Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s friend last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.93,0:19:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it for Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.72,0:19:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was for Madam Tomoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.60,0:19:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, his friend, and Madam\NTomoko were in the same theater circle in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.86,0:19:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she answered the call, the mistress was very nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.36,0:20:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't call me! And don't say weird things!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I smell something fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.24,0:20:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know this person's phone number?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.25,0:20:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.38,0:20:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If anything comes up, we're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.09,0:20:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.67,0:20:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not him either. He has a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.72,0:20:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he got a speechless call last night, and saw it\Nwas Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone number in the call history.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tried to call her back on her cell phone numerous times...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.27,0:20:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But couldn't get in contact with\Nher, so he tried on the land line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.73,0:20:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sure is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.77,0:20:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mistress' phone should have been\Nlocked since she lost it the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.82,0:20:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the person with her cell\Nphone unlocked it, then used it to call this friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then that could be a motive for the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.33,0:20:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of e-mails from the partner she was in an\Naffair with were stored in the phone's memory, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.21,0:20:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that person is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:20:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you found her cell phone\Nsoon after you arrived here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.67,0:21:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. She found it herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, I didn't ask her where she found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.89,0:21:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. You gathered all the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.73,0:21:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to call Shinichi, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.90,0:21:18.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.48,0:21:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when you call him, I'll take the phone and I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll talk to him directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.32,0:21:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.31,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He definitely couldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.17,0:21:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.57,0:21:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.66,0:21:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you know that the combination on a\Ncell phone's lock is a four-digit number, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.54,0:21:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 0000 to 9999, there are 10,000 different combinations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.21,0:21:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even I couldn't try them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.67,0:21:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I had a ton of free time, and was an invisible\Nman that no one could see, that'd be a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Invisible man?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.05,0:21:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, even if it only took them 3\Nseconds per number, it'd take 30,000 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.60,0:21:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.60,0:21:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any normal person would have given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.69,0:22:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the person who unlocked it\Nwasn't disturbed by anyone for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.98,0:22:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's one of those three who\Nwere confined to their rooms the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.80,0:22:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my daily life, where I could see no tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that I fell in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.47,0:22:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never want these feelings to change...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.27,0:22:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So stop time, and preserve the present that echoes throughout my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was once afraid to be together with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.45,0:22:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But although I can't change others or the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.71,0:23:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can change myself and my dreams for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.14,0:23:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.43,0:23:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As sorrow piles up in the darkening city.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.56,0:23:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forever in a soft, warm breeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.32,0:23:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We 'll be together, believing in each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.62,0:23:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,June Bride, I'll be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.46,0:23:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll send that mail one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.51,0:23:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'll catch you this time for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.34,0:23:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So whose pipe could that have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.47,0:23:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying there's a double of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.85,0:23:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A double?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.35,0:24:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since you police came to this house, I haven't been able\Nto concentrate and haven't finished writing a single line!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.85,0:24:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I can only think of one other possible explanation...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.07,0:24:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is actually... Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.65,0:24:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: The Strange Family's Request, Part 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.08,0:24:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.03,0:24:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case from 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.00,0:24:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.07,0:24:22.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The new ending theme is "June Bride"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.21,0:24:23.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's like our special song, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.54,0:24:24.70,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You do realize that Sato isn't here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.70,0:24:25.75,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I-I know that!
